Stay Safe Online – Checklist

Don’t click on random links in emails or messages, especially if they say something urgent
Always check the sender’s email ID properly before trusting any message
Use strong passwords and don’t keep the same password for everything
Turn on two-factor authentication (OTP/login verification) wherever possible
Avoid using public Wi-Fi for logging into important accounts like banking or email
Don’t share personal details like OTPs, passwords, or ID proofs with anyone online

For UPI / Financial Safety:

Never approve a UPI “collect request” unless you are sure you are receiving money (not sending it)
Don’t scan unknown QR codes or trust messages asking for payment refunds or rewards

If something goes wrong:

Report immediately on the National Cyber Crime Portal: https://cybercrime.gov.in
Call the cybercrime helpline: 1930.
